latestIgtvVideos.title: Skincare for Beginners (Or Anyone)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This video is pretty much everything I’d say to someone who’s interested in skincare and finds themselves a bit confused by all the information out there - or someone who just wants a nice easy to follow yet effective routine that doesn’t necessarily have to involve a lot of products. 
Skincare really is simpler than we think, and consistency is key! I hope this is helpful and if you find it helpful share with anyone you know who wants to figure out skincare but doesn’t know where to start.❤️ 

P.S. Ignore my hair because even I know it's a mess at the moment & it's just my hair's way of telling me to go get some cut & color done :)

latestIgtvVideos.title: Episode 2: Styling a Plain Sari in Three Ways ♥️ Which one is your fave?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Always wanted to do a styling video with a Sari. I’m using a plain Sari in Blue (Satin Crepe material) which has a very nice fall. For the Blouse, instead of the normal one I went with a wrap around blouse (inspired by @amrita_thakur) but it can also be worn as a plain blouse ♥️ Thanks to @thesvana for creating this gorgeous piece for me ✨
Talking about Styling it in 3 different ways:
Lehenga Look:
I made tiny pleats with the Sari and tucked it all over my waist ( a complete round to where I started and I pinned both the ends together) I brought the leftover Sari towards the front as a dupatta ♥️

latestPosts.caption:
Best of 2023 - Crafts ♥️

This year has been more about making art - playing with watercolors and different canvases for embroidery, recreating and freezing memories through them 🫶🤗

My husband and I always wanted to decorate our house through art, and this year game me some possibilities to create more personalized art! Though it’s a never ending process, it brought us joy and that enhances every time someone steps into our home & appreciates how our home actually feels like home and like a happy & serene lil adobe ♥️ Everything we dreamed of and there’s a long way to go 😀

And hopefully 2024 will be about undertaking some long due big projects at home 🏡 

#bestof2023 #craftsofinstagram #myhomemyvibe #myhappycorner #creatingmemoriesthroughart #freezingmoments #loveforcraft #buildinghome #diyhomes #aestheticvideos❤️ #myhomevibes #homeiswheretheheartis

Also I’m from Vizag and Husband is from Eluru, our mother tongue is Telugu! We are currently living in the US :)

latestPosts.caption:
Turning my favorite dress to a skirt 🌸 
The dress had a 6 year run, and it started splitting up at the seams so, thought it’s time to give it a new life! I absolutely love how buttery soft this fabric is, so couldn’t just stash it away without mending ✨ Probably this will give it a few more years 🎈 

I loved pairing it with this cute shirt, what do you 🤔 Did I do a good job mending this one?

P.S. I don’t take a whiskey or any drink for that matter at all! But my coffee strong to handle the toddler throughout the day 😆

Happy Sunday ✨

Can we really slow down in this fast paced world 🌎 ?

We can, over time, if we intentionally try 🌸

How I like and want most of my weekends to be ♥️ - Slow, fun filled and cozy 🎈

Slow Living| Weekend at home| Simple Pleasures| Everyday Life

latestPosts.caption:
Celebrated 34 on Friday with a sense of gratitude and appreciation for the ‘freedom’ I inherited ♥️ and the ‘joy’ I created with the help of the divine 🥹

A tiny lil family of my own - from being a daughter to now being a mother 🎈Still feels unreal, coz many a days I still feel I’m the child and I find it hard to sink in the fact, in many a ways, on how fast the time is flying and how fast we ended up growing 🥹

A soft and breezy saree for a breezy day by @shop.dhurvi ♥️
Love how light weight it is and the unique color combo 🌸🍃
